  "body": "## Problem\n\n`TestClassify_ParsesRetryAfterHTTPDate` flaked in CI ([run 25336190655](https://github.com/coder/coder/actions/runs/25336190655)):\n\n```\n--- FAIL: coderd/x/chatd/chaterror TestClassify_ParsesRetryAfterHTTPDate (0.00s)\n    classify_test.go:634:\n        Error: \"1.997382403s\" is not greater than or equal to \"2s\"\n```\n\n## Root cause\n\nThe test built a `Retry-After` header from `time.Now().Add(3 * time.Second)` formatted as an HTTP date. `http.TimeFormat` only has 1-second resolution, so on parse-back `time.Until(retryAt)` can land up to ~1s earlier than the requested offset. Combined with scheduling jitter between formatting and parsing, the observed `RetryAfter` can dip noticeably below the 2s lower bound the test was asserting (1.997s in this run).\n\n## Fix\n\nWiden the offset to 10s and loosen the assertion window so the test only verifies that a positive, sane `RetryAfter` is parsed from an HTTP-date `Retry-After` header. The exact magnitude isn't what we care about here \u2014 that's covered by the seconds-based and `Retry-After-Ms`-based tests.\n\nVerified locally with `go test ./coderd/x/chatd/chaterror -run TestClassify_ParsesRetryAfterHTTPDate -count=200` \u2014 passes cleanly.\n\nFixes coder/internal#1512.\n\nCreated on behalf of @kylecarbs.",
